Approximations.
For large values of n, the following gives an approximation of the binomial coefficient based on its relation to the normal distribution
This follows from the bounds on the Central Limit Theorem, taking a normal distribution with the same expectation and variance as the binomial distribution ("np", "np"(1-"p")), centering the probabilities, by setting "p" = 1 - "p" = 1/2, and multiplying both by 2"n".
